**7\. No pull-to-refresh** On iOS, pulling down on a scrollable list is a standard gesture to refresh. There's no implementation for any page (recent, library, home, etc.).

**8\. Keyboard avoidance when typing in modals** When the iOS software keyboard opens over an input inside a modal (Last.fm login, playlist name, settings inputs), the WebView doesn't auto-scroll the focused input into view. You need to add `interactive-widget=resizes-content` to the viewport meta or handle `visualViewport.resize` events.

**9\. No `@capacitor/share` integration** The share button (`getShareUrl()` exists in `utils.js`) uses a plain URL copy. Capacitor's `Share.share()` API would open the native iOS share sheet, which is the expected behaviour for a native app — copy link, AirDrop, Messages, etc. Especially useful for sharing tracks/albums/playlists.

**10\. No `@capacitor/filesystem` or `@capacitor/share` for downloads** The handoff acknowledges this. Currently blobs can't be saved. The concrete fix is: `Filesystem.writeFile()` to the `Documents` directory, then `Share.share({ url })` to present the iOS "Open in Files / Save to Files" sheet. This is the correct native path.

**11\. Volume slider is useless on iOS** iOS doesn't allow JS to control `audio.volume` programmatically — it's always controlled by the hardware buttons. The volume bar in the player is purely cosmetic on device. It should be hidden on `isIos` and replaced with explanatory text, or just hidden entirely.

**12\. Background audio probably breaks when screen locks (incomplete fix)** The `visibilitychange` handler in `player.js` resumes the `AudioContext`, which is correct. But for iOS background audio to actually work, the `<audio>` element must be playing when the screen locks — not via Web Audio routing. If `audioContextManager` is intercepting audio routing (EQ chain), the audio may cut when iOS suspends the WebView's audio context. The existing code in `applyReplayGain` bypasses Web Audio for iOS/Safari, which is right, but there's no explicit check that EQ/effects are fully disabled on iOS (only ReplayGain routing is checked).

**13\. Context menus (`contextmenu` event) don't work on iOS touch** `contextmenu` is not fired on long-press in Capacitor WebView. Long-press for track context menus is handled via `touchstart` + timeout in `events.js`, but queue items in `ui-interactions.js` only have `contextmenu` listener — they'll never show the menu on device.

---

## iOS-Specific Features Worth Adding

**14\. `@capacitor/status-bar` — match status bar to app theme** The status bar will show system default colouring. Use `StatusBar.setStyle({ style: Style.Dark })` and `StatusBar.setBackgroundColor()` to match the dark theme. One call at init.

**15\. `@capacitor/screen-orientation` — lock to portrait or handle landscape** Currently the fullscreen cover view likely breaks in landscape because the controls overlap. Either lock to portrait on iOS or add landscape-specific layout in the fullscreen overlay.

**16\. AirPlay button is already wired (`webkitShowPlaybackTargetPicker`)** This is working — good. No action needed here, just confirming it's solid.

**17\. Remote Command Center / `navigator.mediaSession` — verify lock screen controls work** `setupMediaSession()` exists in `player.js`. Verify the artwork loads correctly on the lock screen — `mediaSession.metadata` requires an absolute `https://` URL for artwork, not a relative path or blob URL. If cover art is served from a CDN, it should work; if it's constructed with a relative path it'll show a blank icon.

**18\. `@capacitor/splash-screen` — control when the splash hides** Without this, Capacitor auto-hides the splash screen immediately, which can cause a flash of unstyled content while `DOMContentLoaded` fires and settings/theme load. Call `SplashScreen.hide()` manually after `modernSettings.waitPending()` and the initial render completes.

---

## Optimizations

**19\. `hapticLight()` is `async` but awaited nowhere useful (and awaited everywhere)** In `events.js`, `hapticMedium()` / `hapticLight()` are `await`\-ed before `player.playNext()` etc. Since haptics are fire-and-forget, this adds latency to every button press. Don't `await` them.

**20\. `scanLocalMediaFolder()` runs on every startup** It's called unconditionally at the end of `DOMContentLoaded`. On iOS it immediately exits (no `handle` in db), but it still does an async IndexedDB lookup on every cold start. Since local files are disabled on iOS, the call should be guarded with `if (!isIos)`.

**21\. Keyboard shortcuts setup is wasted on iOS** `initializeKeyboardShortcuts()` registers a `keydown` listener that will never fire on a touchscreen. Guarding it with `if (!isIos)` removes a pointless event listener.

**22\. Waveform generation hits the network for every track change** `waveformGenerator.getWaveform()` fetches a LOW quality stream URL to generate waveform data. On mobile this is an extra network request per track. There's no cache TTL or persistence — the cache is in-memory only (`waveformGenerator` internal). Consider persisting generated waveforms to IndexedDB keyed by track ID.

**23\. `body.ios-native .track-list button, body.ios-native .btn-icon` rule adds border/background to every button in a track list** This is overly broad — it will style action buttons inside track rows that shouldn't have a pill border (like inline icon buttons that already have their own style). Scope it more tightly.

